    "title": {
      "rendered": "16 Must-Know Stats About Online Fundraising and Social Media"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/16-Must-Know-Stats-About-Online-Fundraising-and-Social-Media-Square.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19702\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-19702\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/16-Must-Know-Stats-About-Online-Fundraising-and-Social-Media-Square-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"16 Must Know Stats About Online Fundraising and Social Media Square\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/16-Must-Know-Stats-About-Online-Fundraising-and-Social-Media-Square.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/16-Must-Know-Stats-About-Online-Fundraising-and-Social-Media-Square.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/16-Must-Know-Stats-About-Online-Fundraising-and-Social-Media-Square.jpg?resize=768%2C768&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/16-Must-Know-Stats-About-Online-Fundraising-and-Social-Media-Square.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/16-Must-Know-Stats-About-Online-Fundraising-and-Social-Media-Square.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/16-Must-Know-Stats-About-Online-Fundraising-and-Social-Media-Square.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>It&#8217;s true that social media is in transition. Facebook Reach is at an all time low. Instagram<i>\u00a0</i>has a new algorithm. Twitter is in flux. And the next Big Thing in social media ?\u00a0<strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/04/11/how-to-get-your-nonprofit-started-on-snapchat/\">Snapchat</a></strong>\u00a0?\u00a0is baffling to many seasoned social media managers.\u00a0<em>But</em> digital and mobile app payments are coming. The global internet population is set to triple in the next four years. The Internet of Things will transform our world. <em>And</em> email ROI and online giving is up, up, up! In reality, the peak years of email, online fundraising, and social media are ahead of us and <a href=\"https://medium.com/@nonprofitorgs/8-mind-blowing-stats-that-speak-to-the-future-of-digital-communications-and-fundraising-60e0a7a0e426#.2cldg51ku\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>the next decade will astound us all</strong></a>.</p>\n<hr />\n<h1>1. Nearly one in three (31.5%) people worldwide donated to charity in 2015 and one in four (24%) volunteered.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/facts-and-stats-about-ngos-worldwide.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19675 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19675\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/NGOfact-2-FB-SMALL.jpg?resize=600%2C600\" alt=\"PIR-Illustrations\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/NGOfact-2-FB-SMALL.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/NGOfact-2-FB-SMALL.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/NGOfact-2-FB-SMALL.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/NGOfact-2-FB-SMALL.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/NGOfact-2-FB-SMALL.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/facts-and-stats-about-ngos-worldwide.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CAF World Giving Index 2015</a></strong></p>\n<h1>2. By 2018, the global population of social media users is projected to grow to 2.44 billion, or 33% of the world population.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://trackmaven.com/blog/2016/03/social-media-trends/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19621 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19621\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/global-social-media-audience.png?resize=600%2C281\" alt=\"global social media audience\" width=\"600\" height=\"281\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/global-social-media-audience.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/global-social-media-audience.png?resize=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://trackmaven.com/blog/2016/03/social-media-trends/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">TrackMaven</a></strong></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">3. Total giving is expected to grow 4.1% in 2016 and 4.3% in 2017. The vast majority\u00a0of the giving will be done by individuals.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://162.211.248.56/index.php/philanthropy-outlook/total-giving/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19685 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19685\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/total-giving-growth.png?resize=600%2C406\" alt=\"total giving growth\" width=\"600\" height=\"406\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/total-giving-growth.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/total-giving-growth.png?resize=300%2C203&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://162.211.248.56/index.php/philanthropy-outlook/total-giving/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Philanthropy Outlook</a></strong></p>\n<h1>4. Matures donate $683 annually. Boomers $478. Gen Xers $465. And Millennials $238.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.abila.com/lpgs/donorloyaltystudy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19608 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-19608\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/how-much-different-generations-give-to-charity.png?resize=600%2C601\" alt=\"how much different generations give to charity\" width=\"600\" height=\"601\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/how-much-different-generations-give-to-charity.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/how-much-different-generations-give-to-charity.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/how-much-different-generations-give-to-charity.png?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/how-much-different-generations-give-to-charity.png?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/how-much-different-generations-give-to-charity.png?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://www.abila.com/lpgs/donorloyaltystudy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abila</a></strong></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">5. Donors 40-59 years old are now the most likely to give online.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.dunhamandcompany.com/2016/01/survey-shows-aging-donors-most-likely-to-give-online/#sthash.GF57cE1T.dpbs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19693 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19693\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Donors40-59NowMostLikelyToGiveOnline_Dunham_2016_website.jpg?resize=600%2C420\" alt=\"Donors40-59NowMostLikelyToGiveOnline_Dunham_2016_website\" width=\"600\" height=\"420\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Donors40-59NowMostLikelyToGiveOnline_Dunham_2016_website.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Donors40-59NowMostLikelyToGiveOnline_Dunham_2016_website.jpg?resize=300%2C210&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://www.dunhamandcompany.com/2016/01/survey-shows-aging-donors-most-likely-to-give-online/#sthash.GF57cE1T.dpbs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Dunham+Company</a></strong></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>6. Millennials</strong> most inspired to give by social media. Gen X and Baby Boomers by email. <em>Prediction:</em> Gen Z will prefer mobile apps.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19689 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19689\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/2016-Global-Giving-Trends-SMALL.png?resize=600%2C494\" alt=\"2016 Global Giving Trends SMALL\" width=\"600\" height=\"494\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/2016-Global-Giving-Trends-SMALL.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/2016-Global-Giving-Trends-SMALL.png?resize=300%2C247&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Global NGO Online Technology Report</a></strong></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">7. 95% of NGOs worldwide have a Facebook Page. 83% have a Twitter Profile. 40% are active on Instagram.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19690 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19690\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Social-Media-Used-By-NGOs-Worldwide-SMALL.png?resize=600%2C494\" alt=\"Social Media Used By NGOs Worldwide SMALL\" width=\"600\" height=\"494\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Social-Media-Used-By-NGOs-Worldwide-SMALL.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Social-Media-Used-By-NGOs-Worldwide-SMALL.png?resize=300%2C247&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Global NGO Online Technology Report</a></strong></p>\n<h1>8. Internet users have an average of 5.5 social media accounts. They are regularly active on 2.8 of those accounts.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.globalwebindex.net/blog/internet-users-have-average-of-5-social-media-accounts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19699 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19699\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/number-of-accounts-worldwide.png?resize=600%2C410\" alt=\"number of accounts worldwide\" width=\"600\" height=\"410\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/number-of-accounts-worldwide.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/number-of-accounts-worldwide.png?resize=300%2C205&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://www.globalwebindex.net/blog/internet-users-have-average-of-5-social-media-accounts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Global Web Index</a></strong></p>\n<h1>9. 18% of all online donations come from mobile device users.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.cdw.com/content/industries/nonprofit/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19687 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19687\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/mobile-giving-stats.jpg?resize=600%2C471\" alt=\"mobile giving stats\" width=\"600\" height=\"471\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/mobile-giving-stats.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/mobile-giving-stats.jpg?resize=300%2C236&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"https://www.cdw.com/content/industries/nonprofit/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CDW</a></strong></p>\n<h1>10. On average, your followers should grow 23% annually on both Facebook and Twitter.</h1>\n<h1><a href=\"http://trackmaven.com/blog/2016/03/social-media-trends/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19623 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-19623 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/global-social-media-growth.png?resize=600%2C440\" alt=\"global social media growth\" width=\"600\" height=\"440\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/global-social-media-growth.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/global-social-media-growth.png?resize=300%2C220&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://trackmaven.com/blog/2016/03/social-media-trends/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">TrackMaven</a></strong></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">11. Short videos, short online articles, and short emails keep donors the most engaged, informed, and inspired to give.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.abila.com/lpgs/donorloyaltystudy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19611 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-19611\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/inspired-giving-engagement.png?resize=600%2C308\" alt=\"inspired giving engagement\" width=\"600\" height=\"308\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/inspired-giving-engagement.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/inspired-giving-engagement.png?resize=300%2C154&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><br />\n</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://www.abila.com/lpgs/donorloyaltystudy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abila</a></strong></p>\n<h1>12. For every 1,000 fundraising emails delivered, a nonprofit raises $44.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://mrbenchmarks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19618 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19618\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Email-Revenue.png?resize=600%2C377\" alt=\"Email Revenue\" width=\"600\" height=\"377\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Email-Revenue.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Email-Revenue.png?resize=300%2C189&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://mrbenchmarks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">M+R Benchmarks Study</a></strong></p>\n<h1>13. For Every 1,000 email subscribers, nonprofits have 355 Facebook follower, 132 Twitter followers, and 19 Instagram followers.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://mrbenchmarks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19619 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19619\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/For-every-1000-email-subscribers.png?resize=600%2C702\" alt=\"For every 1,000 email subscribers\" width=\"600\" height=\"702\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/For-every-1000-email-subscribers.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/For-every-1000-email-subscribers.png?resize=256%2C300&amp;ssl=1 256w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://mrbenchmarks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">M+R Benchmarks Study</a></strong></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>14. 11% of all online giving occurs over the last three days of the year.</strong></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.networkforgood.com/digitalgivingindex/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19679 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19679\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/December-Giving.png?resize=600%2C503\" alt=\"December Giving\" width=\"600\" height=\"503\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/December-Giving.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/December-Giving.png?resize=300%2C252&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://www.networkforgood.com/digitalgivingindex/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Network for Good</a></strong></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">15. Given the opportunity, 48% of American adults would make donations within a mobile app.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.conecomm.com/2014-digital-activism-study\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19680 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19680\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Cone-Communications-Mobile-App.png?resize=600%2C380\" alt=\"Cone Communications Mobile App\" width=\"600\" height=\"380\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Cone-Communications-Mobile-App.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Cone-Communications-Mobile-App.png?resize=300%2C190&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://www.conecomm.com/2014-digital-activism-study\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cone Communications</a></strong></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">16. 42% of nonprofits use WordPress as the Content Management System for their website.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://npengage.com/nonprofit-technology/only-5-content-managment-systems-drive-62-of-nonprofit-websites/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19697 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19697\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/wordpress-nonprofits-2.jpg?resize=600%2C444\" alt=\"wordpress nonprofits 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"444\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/wordpress-nonprofits-2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/wordpress-nonprofits-2.jpg?resize=300%2C222&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://npengage.com/nonprofit-technology/only-5-content-managment-systems-drive-62-of-nonprofit-websites/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">npENGAGE</a></strong></p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\">The 2016 Global NGO Online Technology Report<em><br />\n2,780 NGOs \u2022 133 Countries \u2022 6 Continents<br />\n</em></span></span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-19119 noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-19119\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Report-Cover-JPG-99.jpg?resize=99%2C121\" alt=\"Report Cover JPG 99\" width=\"99\" height=\"121\" /></a>A collaborative research project by the Public Interest Registry and Nonprofit Tech for Good,\u00a0the <strong><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">2016 Global NGO Online Technology Report</a>\u00a0</strong>is based upon the survey results of 2,780 NGOs from Africa, Asia, Australia &amp; Oceania, Europe, North America, and South America. The research\u00a0is unprecedented and provides valuable insight into the global NGO sector and its use of online technology.</p>\n",
      "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
      "rendered": "<p>It&#8217;s true that social media is in transition. Facebook Reach is at an all time low. Instagram\u00a0has a new algorithm. Twitter is in flux. And the next Big Thing in social media ?\u00a0Snapchat\u00a0?\u00a0is baffling to many seasoned social media managers.\u00a0But digital and mobile app payments are coming. The global internet population is set to triple in the next four years. The Internet of Things will transform our world. And email ROI and online giving is up, up, up! In reality, the peak years of email, online fundraising, and social media are ahead of us and the next decade will astound </p>\n",
      "protected": false
    },
